      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOPSPIN (7) won a steeplechase trial here, and his flat form on either side of that is strong. Wasn't far away over 2500m at Pakenham last time. He's proved to be a tidy hurdler who gets weight relief over brushes with the claimer engaged. The one to beat. FIELD OF LIGHTS (3) resumes and has been well prepared for it. His steeples form last preparation suggests he will be very compeditive if presented on song. Stablemate BAZINI (5) also resumes, and he's also had a solid string of leadups. Has Pateman aboard, and we should see more from him this preparation. NOT USUAL DREAM (4) had a jumps trial and then did nothing on the flat at the picnics. Fitter again and he's a safe chaser who won't be too far away.",
